Most DC fast chargers today are multi-stage AC-DC-DC converters with typical end-to-end efficiencies around 92–94%. Even IISc's recent breakthrough only improved this to 95–97%. At megawatt-scale charging (which we'll need for trucks and large fleets), a 5% loss translates to **50 kW of waste heat** per MW, which means: [irjet](https://www.irjet.net/archives/V12/i4/IRJET-V12I4140.pdf)
